feat: real-time flight prices via SerpAPI Google Flights

- Backend: /api/search/flights endpoint using google_flights engine
- resolve_iata() converts any city name to IATA via in-memory cache
  (pre-seeded with 12 CN cities + 10 global destinations) or MiMo AI
  for unknown inputs; recognizes 3-letter input as-is
- FlightSearchReq model with origin/destination/depart/return/adults/lang
- Returns best+other flights with airline, logo, price, duration, stops,
  layover codes, plus a deep-link bookingUrl to Google Flights
- Dedicated SERPAPI_FLIGHTS_KEY env var to use a separate quota
  (falls back to SERPAPI_KEY if not set)

- Frontend: flight search panel below hotel section in dest tab
- Round-trip / one-way toggle
- 8-city departure dropdown (PVG default) + "Other city" option that
  reveals a free-input field accepting city names or IATA codes
- Auto-fills departure D+14, return D+21 as sensible defaults
- Cards show airline logo, route, time, duration, stops with color
  badges (green=direct, amber=1 stop, red=multi-stop), price
- "View all on Google Flights" deep link as footer button

- LANGS: flightTitle/Round/Oneway/From/Depart/Return/Adults/Custom*/
  SearchBtn/Searching/NoResults/Direct/Stops1/StopsN/Duration/BookAll
  added for all 5 languages (zh/en/ja/ko/id)
- applyLang() updates flight section labels on language switch
- READMEs (client + dev) updated with new feature, env var, API doc

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.7 (noreply@anthropic.com)
